>auf äußere Ursache gegründet (d.i. ein Körper beharrt, u.s.w.).

# Commentary

This is truly a perplexing claim, especially given that 

1. Kant thinks we know (at least partially) the essence of matter
2. The essence of a thing consists in the inner determinations of it
3. Matter has no inner determinations

Kant's argument above does, however, point the way towards reconciling
his project in the MFNS and his remarks in various places that we do not
know the inner determinations of any thing.